(86, 'Kola', '<p>In Case of Emergency, please call INEC on 0700-CALL-INEC (0700-2255-4632) 09050858629, 09050858675, 09050858649, 08180958715, 08180958717, 08180958709, 09025038466, 07086945927, 08120183063, 07062896047, 08105119010, 08146697603 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23EkitiDecides2018\">#EkitiDecides2018</a></p>', '09:01:39', '61t8r0ni5n0g42a64i', NULL),
(87, 'Otunba Akinyemi', '<p>As the electorates of my dear state of origin Ekiti state) file out in less than 24hrs to elect the governor that would hold sway for another 4yrs term, the tension and tempo is heightened. Accusations and counter accusations from political parties of different divides. The election of Ekiti state should be a litmus test for the forthcoming 2019 general elections. INEC must get it right and prove to the generality of the public that it is an unbias umpire by setting a level playing ground for all parties and candidates. The security agencies must not be overzealous and must not be partisan in any form, it should work within the ambit of the law and must not molest nor harass the electorates nor the chieftain of any political party. Anything short of the foregoing might be detrimental to the growth of our nascent democracy. The will of the people must be allowed to prevail, no matter whose ox is gored. Our politicians should be reasonable and not allow desperation for power make them do anything that will be antithetical to electoral laws which can further truncate our nascent democracy. God bless Ekiti state Nigerian</p>', '09:07:30', 'a8r31897ig9i2tn8n4', NULL),
(88, 'Otunba Akinyemi', '<p>As the electorates of my dear state of origin Ekiti state) file out in less than 24hrs to elect the governor that would hold sway for another 4yrs term, the tension and tempo is heightened. Accusations and counter accusations from political parties of different divides. The election of Ekiti state should be a litmus test for the forthcoming 2019 general elections. INEC must get it right and prove to the generality of the public that it is an unbias umpire by setting a level playing ground for all parties and candidates. The security agencies must not be overzealous and must not be partisan in any form, it should work within the ambit of the law and must not molest nor harass the electorates nor the chieftain of any political party. Anything short of the foregoing might be detrimental to the growth of our nascent democracy. The will of the people must be allowed to prevail, no matter whose ox is gored. Our politicians should be reasonable and not allow desperation for power make them do anything that will be antithetical to electoral laws which can further truncate our nascent democracy. God bless Ekiti state Nigerian</p>', '09:08:00', 'rgatn57n42ii671000', NULL),
